items.description: An automated machine learning framework for audio, text, image, video, or .CSV files (50+ featurizers and 15+ model trainers). Python 3.6 required.

items.name: MASPY
items.description: A Python Framework for Multi-Agent Programming with Machine Learning

items.name: DoubleML_Workflow
items.description: This repository implements the Double Machine Learning framework for estimating causal effects in high-dimensional or complex settings, combining the strength of machine learning with causal inference.

items.name: PRIMME
items.description: The repository for the Physics-Regulated Interpretable Machine Learning Microstructure Evolution (PRIMME) framework for learning and emulating microstructure grain growth.

items.name: PySpark-ML-Features
items.description: A PySpark implementation of 6 lesser-known Scikit-Learn features optimized for Azure Databricks. This project translates powerful machine learning techniques from Scikit-Learn into PySpark's distributed computing framework.

items.name: Machine-Learning-Analysis-for-Customer-Data
items.description: Machine Learning Analysis Framework for Customer Data

items.name: Flower-PROV
items.description: Provenance-based Dynamic Fine-Tuning of Federated Machine Learning Framework

items.name: CWT-Machine-Learning-on-Single-Channel-EEG
items.description: Repository for files related to A Machine Learning based Comprehensive Framework for Real-Time Drowsiness Detection via Single-Channel Electroencephalogram Signal Analysis

items.name: 3d-ml
items.description: A versatile framework for 3D machine learning built on Pytorch Lightning and Hydra [looking for contributors!]

items.name: LLM
items.description: LLM implementations with AIX machine learning framework.

items.name: Data-and-Codes-for-Integrated-Design-Framework-for-Titanium-Aluminides-Through-Interpretable-ML
items.description: Data and Codes for Integrated Design Framework for Titanium Aluminides Through Interpretable Machine Learning

items.name: Python-Tutorial
items.description: Notebook tutorials for Python Programming Language (Fundamentals, OOP, MVT, Frameworks, Django, Machine Learning, NLP)

items.name: ml-tracker
items.description: A simple CRUD for tracking machine learning aggregates and storing their data. Created to be used alongside pybondi frameworks.

items.name: Garden
items.description: This Python-based framework integrates various data analysis techniques, including statistics, deep learning, and machine learning, enabling users without coding knowledge to easily utilize them through an intuitive graphical user interface (GUI).

items.name: Cancer-prediction
items.description: Machine Learning-Driven Multimodal Diagnostic Framework for Lung Cancer: Integrating Liquid Biopsy and Traditional Techniques

items.name: Machine-Learning-Strat
items.description: A comprehensive machine learning framework for predicting S&P 500 price movements and implementing a data-driven trading strategy across multiple time horizons.

items.name: Predictive_model_for_SP500_Buy_and_Sell_Signals
items.description: The Predictive_model_for_S&P_500_Buy_and_Sell_Signals repository provides a comprehensive framework for forecasting buy and sell signals in the S&P 500 index. Leveraging advanced machine learning techniques, the project aims to assist investors and traders in making informed decisions based on predictive analytics.

items.name: Duplicate-Question-Pair-Analysis-
items.description: Developed a system to detect duplicate question pairs using Python, NLP libraries (NLTK, SpaCy), and machine learning frameworks (Scikit-Learn).

items.name: Code_Alpha_AIChat
items.description: TASK 3: Artificial Intelligence Chatbot Objective: Implement a chatbot with AI capabilities, including:  Natural Language Processing (NLP) to understand user queries.  Machine learning models for automated responses.  Interactive conversation handling.  Implementation: Use AI/ML frameworks like TensorFlow, OpenAIs GPT

items.name: 100_days_of_AI-ML
items.description: A 100-day journey to master Data Science, AI and Machine Learning through daily blogs, hands-on code implementations, and exploration of essential tools and frameworks. Follow along for consistent progress, fun facts, and practical insights to build expertise and unlock better career opportunities!

items.name: Aut-matos
items.description: Autmatos: Autonomous Code Generation Autmatos is an innovative, self-evolving code generation system inspired by the concept of autonomous agents. This cutting-edge project leverages machine learning and artificial intelligence to create a dynamic, adaptive framework

items.name: Machine-Learning-Model-s-Without-External-Libraries
items.description: ML model comparison project with custom implementations of Logistic Regression, KNN, Decision Trees, Nave Bayes, and Linear Regression. Tested on real-world datasets from UCI with a reusable preprocessing pipeline and evaluation framework. No external ML libraries used.
